{{Politics of Bermuda}}
The land area of [[Bermuda]] is divided into nine [[parish]]es.  There are also two defined [[municipality|municipalities]], located in the boundaries of two of the parishes.

{{stack|[[Image:Bermuda-divmap.png|right|300px]]}}

==Parishes==
Bermuda has nine "Parishes", originally called "Tribes".  Each of the nine parishes with the exception of St. George's covers the same land area, (2.31 square miles / 5.97&nbsp;km²).  The Parishes are not [[administrative division]]s, and have no relationship with Bermuda's [[electoral district]]s.

