The '''China–Myanmar border''' is the international border that limits the territory of the [[China|People's Republic of China]] and [[Myanmar]] (formerly ''Burma''). The border begins at [[Hkakabo Razi]] (5881 m), the highest mountain in [[Southeast Asia]], passing through the mountain ranges of [[Jigongshan]] and [[Jiangaosh]] (3302 m). It continues through mountainous areas and a small northern section of the [[Mekong River]], before ending at the border with [[Laos]].

